commitResults.messageTitle: Level-1. Greet, echo, and exit. Implement a skeletal version of Duke that starts by greeting the user, repeat commands entered by the user, and exits when the user types "bye".
Level-2. Add, list. Added the feature to store the text entered by the user and display them back to the user when requested.
Level-3. Mark as done. Add the feature to mark the task as done. Added task class and taskNumberOutOfBoundException.
Level-4. Added 3 classes: Todo, Deadline, Event. They are subclasses of Task.
Level-4. Added 3 classes: Todo, Event, Deadline. They are subclasses of Task. A-TextUiTesting. Construct an input.txt and an EXPECTED.txt. Pass the automated text UI testing.
Level-5. Added handle errors feature. Do regression test.
Level-6. Added delete task feature. Using automated text UI testing to test Duke.
branch-level-7. Add features: auto load and save task lists from hard disk.
branch-level8. Add features: understand date and times.
A-MoreOOP.  A-Packages.
A-JUnit. Add JUnit tests.
Level-9. Add features: find tasks by a keyword, find tasks on a certain date
A-JavaDoc. A-CodingStandard.
A-Gradle. A-CheckStyle. Use gradle to build and run Duke. Use gradle to run unit tests. Use checkStyle to detect coding style violations.
A-Varargs. Use varargs in ui.printMessages() method. Simplify some printMessages() expressions.
GUI.

commitResults.messageBody:
Many problems may occur during file loading and storing, such as file not being found, parent dir does not exist, taskList.txt format is incorrect, and so on.

Adding assertions to this part of the code allow us to better check some exceptions and ensure that the program runs normally.

commitResults.messageTitle: Improve code quality
commitResults.messageBody:
There are several methods that redundantly initialize a new Array when calling ui.printMessage which is a vararg method.

To improve code quality as well as efficiency let's remove the redundant array initializing.

commitResults.messageTitle: Use streams in DateCommand.execute() method
commitResults.messageBody:
DateCommand.execute() method find the tasks on a specific day by scanning through all the tasks in the list. This part of code is a bit too long and the efficiency is low.

Using streams in this method allows us to make the code clear. It also allows us to use parallel stream to speed up this method if possible.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add extension C-Sort
commitResults.messageBody: Adding a sort-by-time feature allows users to sort their tasks by deadline.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add new feature: sort by time.
commitResults.messageBody: This new feature allows us to sort the tasks in the current task list by their time.
